TITLE: Instruction Type Definition for Tree Item Operations
DESCRIPTION: Defines the Instruction type which represents the possible operations (reorder-above, reorder-below, make-child, reparent) that can be performed when dragging a tree item.
SOURCE: https://github.com/atlassian/pragmatic-drag-and-drop/blob/main/packages/hitbox/constellation/index/about.mdx#2025-04-14_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type Instruction =
	| {
			type: 'reorder-above';
			currentLevel: number;
			indentPerLevel: number;
	  }
	| {
			type: 'reorder-below';
			currentLevel: number;
			indentPerLevel: number;
	  }
	| {
			type: 'make-child';
			currentLevel: number;
			indentPerLevel: number;
	  }
	| {
			type: 'reparent';
			currentLevel: number;
			indentPerLevel: number;
			desiredLevel: number;
	  }
	| {
			type: 'instruction-blocked';
			desired: Exclude<Instruction, { type: 'instruction-blocked' }>;
	  };
```

