TITLE: Defining Base Event Payload Types in TypeScript for Drag and Drop
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the base types for event payloads in drag and drop operations. It includes types for the base payload, drag payload, and a map of all element events.
SOURCE: https://github.com/atlassian/pragmatic-drag-and-drop/blob/main/packages/documentation/constellation/05-core-package/00-adapters/00-element/about.mdx#2025-04-14_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type ElementEventBasePayload = {
	location: DragLocationHistory;
	source: ElementDragPayload;
};

type ElementDragPayload = {
	element: HTMLElement;
	dragHandle: Element | null;
	data: Record<string, unknown>;
};

type ElementEventPayloadMap = {
	onDragStart: ElementEventBasePayload;
	// .. the rest of the events
};
```

